      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#7 TEAM WORKFLOWS · $42/MO</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Loomly — Best for small businesses with a team managing social</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For small businesses where 2-4 people collaborate on social content and need defined approval workflows.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Loomly structures post workflows from ideation through approval to publishing. For a small business where the owner needs to approve every post before it goes live, this is the right tool. Automatic post ideas from trending topics help when your team runs dry. $42/mo starting price is high for solo operators — justified only if multiple people manage your social accounts.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Multi-stage approval workflow — owner approves before anything publishes</h4><p>Perfect for small businesses where the founder reviews all social content before it goes live.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Automatic post ideas from trending topics and events</h4><p>Content idea generation built in — useful when your team runs low on inspiration.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Content library for shared brand assets</h4><p>Store approved photos, brand guidelines, and copy assets in one place the whole team accesses.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: $42/mo is overkill for solo operators</h4><p>If you're the only person managing social, Loomly's collaboration features don't justify the price.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
