        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#8 ENTERPRISE PICK · $99/MO</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Hootsuite — Best for small businesses that are growing into enterprise</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For businesses that have outgrown Buffer and now manage 5+ accounts with a small team.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Hootsuite is too expensive and too complex for most small businesses. At $99/mo for a single user, it costs more than theStacc's done-for-you content service. But if you've grown to 5+ social accounts and need multi-user workflows, social listening, and bulk scheduling, Hootsuite is the platform built for that transition. Don't start here — grow into it.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Multi-user approval workflows for growing teams</h4><p>When you hire a social media person, Hootsuite gives them proper permission controls.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Social listening — know when your brand is mentioned</h4><p>Track brand mentions across the web, not just your tagged posts.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Comprehensive content calendar for 10+ accounts</h4><p>Managing multiple brand accounts in one view is where Hootsuite genuinely excels.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: $99/mo minimum with a steep learning curve</h4><p>Small businesses pay for features they don't use. Buffer at $6/mo or theStacc at $49/mo serves most small businesses better.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

